<font face="Serif" size="18">Jesus, and many, many others</font>

1066
00:59:22,442 --> 00:59:24,744
<font face="Serif" size="18">—they all trusted in Jehovah,</font>

1067
00:59:24,744 --> 00:59:29,616
<font face="Serif" size="18">and Jehovah never failed
to make them equal to the pressure.</font>

1068
00:59:29,616 --> 00:59:32,252
<font face="Serif" size="18">He’ll do the same for you.</font>

1069
00:59:32,252 --> 00:59:34,687
<font face="Serif" size="18">And so in conclusion,</font>

1070
00:59:34,687 --> 00:59:38,291
<font face="Serif" size="18">you see, it really doesn’t matter</font>

1071
00:59:38,291 --> 00:59:40,293
<font face="Serif" size="18">how great the pressure is.</font>

1072
00:59:40,293 --> 00:59:43,896
<font face="Serif" size="18">It only matters where the pressure lies.</font>

1073
00:59:43,896 --> 00:59:47,500
<font face="Serif" size="18">Do not let it come between you</font>

1074
00:59:47,500 --> 00:59:51,170
<font face="Serif" size="18">and Jehovah
and your worship and service.</font>

1075
00:59:51,170 --> 00:59:53,773
<font face="Serif" size="18">Don’t let it come between you,</font>

1076
00:59:53,773 --> 00:59:56,843
<font face="Serif" size="18">because then the external pressure</font>

1077
00:59:56,843 --> 01:00:00,413
<font face="Serif" size="18">will only continue to move you closer</font>

1078
01:00:00,413 --> 01:00:03,383
<font face="Serif" size="18">to your heavenly Father.</font>

1079
01:00:03,383 --> 01:00:07,553
<font face="Serif" size="18">The life that flourishes
in the Mariana Trench gives</font>

1080
01:00:07,553 --> 01:00:10,556
<font face="Serif" size="18">a positive example, a beautiful example,</font>

1081
01:00:10,556 --> 01:00:13,660
<font face="Serif" size="18">of Jehovah’s limitless ability
to help his creation</font>

1082
01:00:13,660 --> 01:00:15,662
<font face="Serif" size="18">deal with pressure.</font>

1083
01:00:15,662 --> 01:00:17,997
<font face="Serif" size="18">Prayer, trust, and patience</font>

1084
01:00:17,997 --> 01:00:21,634
<font face="Serif" size="18">will always be rewarded by Jehovah.</font>

1085
01:00:21,634 --> 01:00:24,304
<font face="Serif" size="18">Relief will come.</font>

1086
01:00:24,304 --> 01:00:27,073
<font face="Serif" size="18">So remain close to your heavenly Father,</font>

1087
01:00:27,073 --> 01:00:30,209
<font face="Serif" size="18">and you will not just survive</font>

1088
01:00:30,209 --> 01:00:33,212
<font face="Serif" size="18">the pressure in the trench</font>

1089
01:00:33,212 --> 01:00:35,948
<font face="Serif" size="18">but you will thrive spiritually.</font>

1090
01:00:42,789 --> 01:00:47,126
<font face="Serif" size="18">Thank you, Brother Cauthon,
for your nice, insightful comments</font>

1091
01:00:47,126 --> 01:00:49,128
<font face="Serif" size="18">—much appreciated.</font>

1092
01:00:49,128 --> 01:00:51,798
<font face="Serif" size="18">Now, our third interview involves a brother</font>

1093
01:00:51,798 --> 01:00:54,701
<font face="Serif" size="18">who serves as a member
of the Branch Committee</font>

1094
01:00:54,701 --> 01:00:56,903
<font face="Serif" size="18">in Sri Lanka.</font>

1095
01:00:56,903 --> 01:01:01,874
<font face="Serif" size="18">He graduated from the 146th class of Gilead</font>

1096
01:01:01,874 --> 01:01:04,644
<font face="Serif" size="18">—so just four classes back.</font>

1097
01:01:04,644 --> 01:01:06,779
<font face="Serif" size="18">Listen carefully as he explains</font>

1098
01:01:06,779 --> 01:01:11,751
<font face="Serif" size="18">how Gilead training helped him
to see things about his personality</font>

1099
01:01:11,751 --> 01:01:14,020
<font face="Serif" size="18">that he needed to refine</font>

1100
01:01:14,020 --> 01:01:18,491
<font face="Serif" size="18">to become a stabilizing
and strengthening influence</font>

1101
01:01:18,491 --> 01:01:20,493
<font face="Serif" size="18">in his branch territory.</font>

1102
01:01:22,829 --> 01:01:25,765
<font face="Serif" size="18">Brother and Sister Sivakumaran
will be returning to Sri Lanka.</font>

1103
01:01:28,835 --> 01:01:30,870
<font face="Serif" size="18">In Gilead, the wonderful thing</font>

1104
01:01:30,870 --> 01:01:32,739
<font face="Serif" size="18">is that you get to learn
from the beginning</font>

1105
01:01:32,739 --> 01:01:34,607
<font face="Serif" size="18">Jehovah’s dealings with humankind,</font>

1106
01:01:34,607 --> 01:01:36,075
<font face="Serif" size="18">that vast history.</font>

1107
01:01:36,075 --> 01:01:37,910
<font face="Serif" size="18">Learning that is humbling.</font>

1108
01:01:39,379 --> 01:01:41,414
<font face="Serif" size="18">How tiny I am</font>

1109
01:01:41,414 --> 01:01:43,449
<font face="Serif" size="18">and the small role that I play</font>

1110
01:01:43,449 --> 01:01:45,818
<font face="Serif" size="18">in Jehovah’s organization are a realization!</font>

1111
01:01:45,818 --> 01:01:50,189
<font face="Serif" size="18">Before going to Gilead,
I thought I was a loving person,</font>

1112
01:01:50,189 --> 01:01:53,159
<font face="Serif" size="18">because we always think
we want to be loving people.</font>

1113
01:01:53,159 --> 01:01:56,629
<font face="Serif" size="18">But during Gilead,
it was made aware to me</font>

1114
01:01:56,629 --> 01:01:59,332
<font face="Serif" size="18">that I had a spiritual blind spot.</font>

1115
01:01:59,332 --> 01:02:02,969
<font face="Serif" size="18">There were brothers and sisters
that I didn’t really notice before,</font>

1116
01:02:04,971 --> 01:02:07,840
<font face="Serif" size="18">and that kind of taught me
an important lesson.</font>

1117
01:02:07,840 --> 01:02:10,910
<font face="Serif" size="18">It’s not about giving talks,</font>

1118
01:02:10,910 --> 01:02:15,081
<font face="Serif" size="18">but really it’s personal attention
that brothers need.</font>

1119
01:02:15,081 --> 01:02:17,216
<font face="Serif" size="18">So I need to give them my time,</font>

1120
01:02:17,216 --> 01:02:19,318
<font face="Serif" size="18">and I need to help them understand</font>

1121
01:02:19,318 --> 01:02:22,955
<font face="Serif" size="18">that Jehovah loves them very much.</font>

1122
01:02:22,955 --> 01:02:27,860
<font face="Serif" size="18">You know, one word that stands out
throughout the training is “mercy.”</font>

1123
01:02:27,860 --> 01:02:29,295
<font face="Serif" size="18">Israel made many mistakes,</font>

1124
01:02:29,295 --> 01:02:31,597
<font face="Serif" size="18">but Jehovah never picked on them
for their mistakes.</font>

1125
01:02:31,597 --> 01:02:35,268
<font face="Serif" size="18">He just wanted them to come back to him,
and that was a lovely lesson.</font>

1126
01:02:35,268 --> 01:02:39,639
<font face="Serif" size="18">As an overseer,
I need to ask a question that always,</font>

1127
01:02:39,639 --> 01:02:41,941
<font face="Serif" size="18">you know, rings in my my ear,</font>

1128
01:02:41,941 --> 01:02:45,378
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘Am I going to criticize,
or am I going to commend?’</font>

1129
01:02:45,378 --> 01:02:48,581
<font face="Serif" size="18">Just to give you an example,
before going to Gilead,</font>

1130
01:02:48,581 --> 01:02:52,251
<font face="Serif" size="18">as a home overseer
I was strict</font>

1131
01:02:52,251 --> 01:02:55,488
<font face="Serif" size="18">and came across stingy,
to be honest.</font>

1132
01:02:55,488 --> 01:02:58,624
<font face="Serif" size="18">But during Gilead,
it was made well aware to me</font>

1133
01:02:58,624 --> 01:03:00,426
<font face="Serif" size="18">that I need to change.</font>

1134
01:03:00,426 --> 01:03:02,662
<font face="Serif" size="18">I need to be more generous,</font>

1135
01:03:02,662 --> 01:03:04,897
<font face="Serif" size="18">and I need to be merciful.</font>

1136
01:03:04,897 --> 01:03:07,600
<font face="Serif" size="18">I vividly remember that one instructor said:</font>

1137
01:03:07,600 --> 01:03:11,637
<font face="Serif" size="18">“Saying no to everything can be addictive,</font>

1138
01:03:11,637 --> 01:03:13,639
<font face="Serif" size="18">and it makes for an easy way out.”</font>

1139
01:03:13,639 --> 01:03:18,344
<font face="Serif" size="18">But we were admonished
to say yes whenever we can</font>

1140
01:03:18,344 --> 01:03:20,713
<font face="Serif" size="18">and to help the brothers.</font>

1141
01:03:20,713 --> 01:03:24,283
<font face="Serif" size="18">Summing up Gilead,
I can’t do better than Jesus.</font>

1142
01:03:24,283 --> 01:03:27,753
<font face="Serif" size="18">Love Jehovah; love people</font>

1143
01:03:27,753 --> 01:03:29,856
<font face="Serif" size="18">—that’s the whole training of Gilead.</font>

1144
01:03:29,856 --> 01:03:31,891
<font face="Serif" size="18">And some of my feelings</font>

1145
01:03:31,891 --> 01:03:36,295
<font face="Serif" size="18">every time I think about Gilead</font>

1146
01:03:36,295 --> 01:03:40,600
<font face="Serif" size="18">are that I have a long way to go
to put all those details into practice</font>

1147
01:03:40,600 --> 01:03:43,970
<font face="Serif" size="18">and to change myself to fit Jehovah.</font>

1148
01:03:43,970 --> 01:03:46,973
<font face="Serif" size="18">So, yeah, I have a long way to go,
so I’m working on it.</font>

1149
01:03:53,980 --> 01:03:58,384
<font face="Serif" size="18">So we pray that all
of you soon-to-be graduates</font>

1150
01:03:58,384 --> 01:04:01,153
<font face="Serif" size="18">examine yourself to ensure</font>

1151
01:04:01,153 --> 01:04:05,258
<font face="Serif" size="18">that you’ll have a strengthening effect
on the brotherhood.</font>

1152
01:04:05,258 --> 01:04:08,461
<font face="Serif" size="18">It was nice, the humble expressions
he shared with us.</font>

1153
01:04:08,461 --> 01:04:12,965
<font face="Serif" size="18">Now let’s turn our attention
to another one of the Gilead instructors</font>

1154
01:04:12,965 --> 01:04:16,936
<font face="Serif" size="18">and a helper to the Teaching Committee,
Mark Noumair.</font>

1155
01:04:16,936 --> 01:04:19,472
<font face="Serif" size="18">The title of his talk is</font>

1156
01:04:19,472 --> 01:04:24,243
<font face="Serif" size="18">“‘I Cling to You; You Hold on to Me.’”</font>

1157
01:04:24,243 --> 01:04:26,245
<font face="Serif" size="18">Brother Noumair.</font>

1158
01:04:28,347 --> 01:04:32,718
<font face="Serif" size="18">In this talk, we want you to understand</font>

1159
01:04:32,718 --> 01:04:37,490
<font face="Serif" size="18">the sustaining power of loyal love.</font>

1160
01:04:37,490 --> 01:04:40,459
<font face="Serif" size="18">Because it is this quality, loyal love,</font>

1161
01:04:40,459 --> 01:04:42,528
<font face="Serif" size="18">and its power</font>

1162
01:04:42,528 --> 01:04:46,032
<font face="Serif" size="18">that will help you face future trials</font>

1163
01:04:46,032 --> 01:04:50,469
<font face="Serif" size="18">and challenges with confidence in Jehovah.</font>

1164
01:04:50,469 --> 01:04:53,639
<font face="Serif" size="18">Well, you perhaps remember the definition</font>

1165
01:04:53,639 --> 01:04:56,409
<font face="Serif" size="18">of loyal love from a written review.</font>

1166
01:04:56,409 --> 01:05:00,680
<font face="Serif" size="18">But it’s this: It is love motivated</font>

1167
01:05:00,680 --> 01:05:04,784
<font face="Serif" size="18">by a strong commitment and a deep attachment.</font>

1168
01:05:04,784 --> 01:05:06,986
<font face="Serif" size="18">And here’s how King David described</font>

1169
01:05:06,986 --> 01:05:11,257
<font face="Serif" size="18">the loyal love that existed
between him and Jehovah.</font>

1170
01:05:11,257 --> 01:05:14,160
<font face="Serif" size="18">He said at Psalm 63:8:</font>

1171
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:16,529
<font face="Serif" size="18">“I cling to you;</font>

1172
01:05:16,529 --> 01:05:20,499
<font face="Serif" size="18">your right hand keeps fast hold on me.”</font>

1173
01:05:20,499 --> 01:05:23,269
<font face="Serif" size="18">Now, this is loyal love,</font>

1174
01:05:23,269 --> 01:05:25,271
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘I cling to you.</font>

1175
01:05:25,271 --> 01:05:28,240
<font face="Serif" size="18">You hold on to me.’</font>

1176
01:05:28,240 --> 01:05:30,977
<font face="Serif" size="18">Now, in the first century
—a woman—</font>

1177
01:05:30,977 --> 01:05:33,679
<font face="Serif" size="18">a woman who set an outstanding example</font>

1178
01:05:33,679 --> 01:05:37,817
<font face="Serif" size="18">of clinging to Jehovah is Anna.</font>

1179
01:05:37,817 --> 01:05:40,453
<font face="Serif" size="18">How so?
Let’s find out.</font>

1180
01:05:40,453 --> 01:05:43,556
<font face="Serif" size="18">We open our Bibles to Luke chapter 2.</font>

1181
01:05:43,556 --> 01:05:46,726
<font face="Serif" size="18">We’re going to read verses 36 and 37</font>

1182
01:05:46,726 --> 01:05:51,130
<font face="Serif" size="18">and see what lesson
we can learn and apply to you:</font>

1183
01:05:53,866 --> 01:05:55,468
<font face="Serif" size="18">“Now there was a prophetess,</font>

1184
01:05:55,468 --> 01:05:58,971
<font face="Serif" size="18">“Anna the daughter
of Phanuel, of Asher’s tribe.</font>

1185
01:05:58,971 --> 01:06:01,207
<font face="Serif" size="18">“This woman was well along in years</font>

1186
01:06:01,207 --> 01:06:05,544
<font face="Serif" size="18">“and had lived with her husband
for seven years after they were married,</font>

1187
01:06:05,544 --> 01:06:09,382
<font face="Serif" size="18">“and she was a widow now 84 years old.</font>

1188
01:06:09,382 --> 01:06:11,884
<font face="Serif" size="18">“She was never missing from the temple,</font>

1189
01:06:11,884 --> 01:06:14,954
<font face="Serif" size="18">“rendering sacred service night and day</font>

1190
01:06:14,954 --> 01:06:17,590
<font face="Serif" size="18">with fasting and supplications.”</font>

1191
01:06:17,590 --> 01:06:19,792
<font face="Serif" size="18">Well, here we have it.</font>

1192
01:06:19,792 --> 01:06:23,629
<font face="Serif" size="18">Everything we know about Anna is right here.</font>

1193
01:06:23,629 --> 01:06:25,931
<font face="Serif" size="18">Luke recorded it.</font>

1194
01:06:25,931 --> 01:06:28,534
<font face="Serif" size="18">She was 84 years old</font>

1195
01:06:28,534 --> 01:06:31,771
<font face="Serif" size="18">when Luke introduces her to us.</font>

1196
01:06:31,771 --> 01:06:36,475
<font face="Serif" size="18">Likely, she hadn’t lived long enough
to become a follower of Jesus,</font>

1197
01:06:36,475 --> 01:06:39,011
<font face="Serif" size="18">to be anointed with holy spirit,</font>

1198
01:06:39,011 --> 01:06:42,148
<font face="Serif" size="18">or to enjoy preaching
the good news of the Kingdom.</font>

1199
01:06:42,148 --> 01:06:44,216
<font face="Serif" size="18">That’s it.</font>

1200
01:06:44,216 --> 01:06:47,887
<font face="Serif" size="18"><i>If</i></font><font face="Serif" size="18">  we stop right there.</font>

1201
01:06:47,887 --> 01:06:49,989
<font face="Serif" size="18">But what if we don’t?</font>

1202
01:06:49,989 --> 01:06:52,358
<font face="Serif" size="18">What if we dig deeper?</font>

1203
01:06:52,358 --> 01:06:55,094
<font face="Serif" size="18">What will we learn that will help you?</font>

1204
01:06:55,094 --> 01:06:57,096
<font face="Serif" size="18">Well, let’s do that.</font>

1205
01:06:57,863 --> 01:07:01,734
<font face="Serif" size="18">Anna was born about 86 B.C.E.</font>

1206
01:07:03,302 --> 01:07:06,038
<font face="Serif" size="18">When she was 23 years old,</font>

1207
01:07:06,038 --> 01:07:10,776
<font face="Serif" size="18">Jerusalem was filled
with violence and divisions.</font>

1208
01:07:10,776 --> 01:07:13,713
<font face="Serif" size="18">Jewish leaders
such as the Maccabees are at war.</font>

1209
01:07:13,713 --> 01:07:17,383
<font face="Serif" size="18">Roman forces under the leadership
of a soldier named Pompey</font>

1210
01:07:17,383 --> 01:07:20,252
<font face="Serif" size="18">came to restore order, and in the process,</font>

1211
01:07:20,252 --> 01:07:24,924
<font face="Serif" size="18">some 12,000 Jews reportedly died.</font>

1212
01:07:24,924 --> 01:07:28,394
<font face="Serif" size="18">It is possible that Anna’s husband</font>

1213
01:07:28,394 --> 01:07:30,463
<font face="Serif" size="18">was one of these victims.</font>

1214
01:07:31,530 --> 01:07:34,700
<font face="Serif" size="18">Then when Anna was 47 years old,</font>

1215
01:07:34,700 --> 01:07:37,603
<font face="Serif" size="18">the Romans appointed Herod as king of Judea.</font>

1216
01:07:37,603 --> 01:07:39,305
<font face="Serif" size="18">Herod?</font>

1217
01:07:39,305 --> 01:07:41,474
<font face="Serif" size="18">This man was not a descendant of David.</font>

1218
01:07:41,474 --> 01:07:43,476
<font face="Serif" size="18">He was not even an Israelite.</font>

1219
01:07:43,476 --> 01:07:45,511
<font face="Serif" size="18">He was an Edomite.</font>

1220
01:07:45,511 --> 01:07:49,849
<font face="Serif" size="18">The Edomites
were sworn enemies of true worship.</font>

1221
01:07:49,849 --> 01:07:54,553
<font face="Serif" size="18">Now, on top of that,
the hypocritical Jewish religious leaders</font>

1222
01:07:54,553 --> 01:07:59,558
<font face="Serif" size="18">made life hard for people,
including widows like Anna.</font>

1223
01:07:59,558 --> 01:08:03,829
<font face="Serif" size="18">So now Anna watches
as Jehovah’s “house of prayer,”</font>

1224
01:08:03,829 --> 01:08:08,467
<font face="Serif" size="18">the place she cherished,
became “a cave of robbers.”</font>

1225
01:08:08,467 --> 01:08:12,538
<font face="Serif" size="18">Pure worship is withering on the vine.</font>

1226
01:08:12,538 --> 01:08:14,540
<font face="Serif" size="18">What will Anna do?</font>

1227
01:08:14,540 --> 01:08:16,609
<font face="Serif" size="18">She could have been stumbled.</font>

1228
01:08:16,609 --> 01:08:21,447
<font face="Serif" size="18">She could have reasoned:
‘I supported true worship all my life.</font>

1229
01:08:21,447 --> 01:08:25,918
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘I believed the Messiah would come
and the prophecies would come.</font>

1230
01:08:25,918 --> 01:08:27,987
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘I go to the temple every day.</font>

1231
01:08:27,987 --> 01:08:31,690
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘I’ve done everything right,
but things have only gotten worse.</font>

1232
01:08:31,690 --> 01:08:36,128
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘God let my husband die;
an Edomite is rebuilding the temple.</font>

1233
01:08:36,128 --> 01:08:38,130
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘What’s happening?</font>

1234
01:08:38,130 --> 01:08:40,332
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘Has Jehovah left us?</font>

1235
01:08:40,332 --> 01:08:42,501
<font face="Serif" size="18">Should I leave too?’</font>

1236
01:08:43,569 --> 01:08:46,739
<font face="Serif" size="18">Anna could have given up,
walked away, became bitter.</font>

1237
01:08:46,739 --> 01:08:48,741
<font face="Serif" size="18">But she didn’t.</font>

1238
01:08:48,741 --> 01:08:51,310
<font face="Serif" size="18">Why? Why?</font>

1239
01:08:51,310 --> 01:08:54,647
<font face="Serif" size="18">It was the roots of her loyal love,</font>

1240
01:08:54,647 --> 01:08:56,982
<font face="Serif" size="18">that sustaining power of loyal love.</font>

1241
01:08:56,982 --> 01:09:00,119
<font face="Serif" size="18">It went deep, and it wrapped around Jehovah.</font>

1242
01:09:00,119 --> 01:09:03,122
<font face="Serif" size="18">And she had the power to keep clinging to him</font>

1243
01:09:03,122 --> 01:09:05,624
<font face="Serif" size="18">under those circumstances.</font>

1244
01:09:05,624 --> 01:09:09,662
<font face="Serif" size="18">Anna was determined to serve Jehovah
to the best of her ability.</font>

1245
01:09:10,462 --> 01:09:11,664
<font face="Serif" size="18">What did she do?</font>

1246
01:09:11,664 --> 01:09:15,901
<font face="Serif" size="18">Again, looking at verse 37:</font>

1247
01:09:15,901 --> 01:09:19,238
<font face="Serif" size="18">“She was never missing from the temple,</font>

1248
01:09:19,238 --> 01:09:21,407
<font face="Serif" size="18">“[She was in the right place.]</font>

1249
01:09:23,309 --> 01:09:26,645
<font face="Serif" size="18">“rendering sacred service night and day</font>

1250
01:09:26,645 --> 01:09:29,315
<font face="Serif" size="18">“[doing the right thing]</font>

1251
01:09:29,315 --> 01:09:31,851
<font face="Serif" size="18">“with fasting and supplications</font>

1252
01:09:31,851 --> 01:09:34,587
<font face="Serif" size="18">[with the right attitude].”</font>

1253
01:09:34,587 --> 01:09:37,723
<font face="Serif" size="18">She was doing the right thing</font>

1254
01:09:37,723 --> 01:09:41,260
<font face="Serif" size="18">in the right place with the right attitude.</font>

1255
01:09:41,260 --> 01:09:45,464
<font face="Serif" size="18">Nothing could stop
this seemingly fragile servant of God</font>

1256
01:09:45,464 --> 01:09:48,467
<font face="Serif" size="18">from clinging to her closest Friend, Jehovah.</font>

1257
01:09:49,735 --> 01:09:52,438
<font face="Serif" size="18">In effect, Anna was saying,</font>

1258
01:09:52,438 --> 01:09:56,175
<font face="Serif" size="18">“I cling to you, Jehovah.”</font>

1259
01:09:56,175 --> 01:09:59,345
<font face="Serif" size="18">And her loyal love was noticed.</font>

1260
01:10:00,779 --> 01:10:03,415
<font face="Serif" size="18">Chapter 2 and verse 38</font>

1261
01:10:03,415 --> 01:10:06,552
<font face="Serif" size="18">reveals that Anna was present</font>

1262
01:10:06,552 --> 01:10:10,422
<font face="Serif" size="18">when the baby Jesus
was brought to the temple.</font>

1263
01:10:10,422 --> 01:10:15,227
<font face="Serif" size="18">And when she saw that baby,
what did she begin to do in verse 38?</font>

1264
01:10:15,227 --> 01:10:19,531
<font face="Serif" size="18">It says: “She came near
and [she] began giving thanks to God</font>

1265
01:10:19,531 --> 01:10:22,501
<font face="Serif" size="18">“and speaking about the child
to all who were waiting</font>

1266
01:10:22,501 --> 01:10:25,037
<font face="Serif" size="18">for Jerusalem’s deliverance.”</font>

1267
01:10:25,037 --> 01:10:27,940
<font face="Serif" size="18">Can you sense her joy?</font>

1268
01:10:27,940 --> 01:10:31,410
<font face="Serif" size="18">Can you feel the joy she had
at seeing and, perhaps, even holding</font>

1269
01:10:31,410 --> 01:10:33,946
<font face="Serif" size="18">that little baby, the future Messiah?</font>

1270
01:10:33,946 --> 01:10:36,649
<font face="Serif" size="18">This was something that this elderly woman</font>

1271
01:10:36,649 --> 01:10:40,185
<font face="Serif" size="18">had never expected in her lifetime.</font>

1272
01:10:40,185 --> 01:10:43,856
<font face="Serif" size="18">The child in front of her was proof</font>

1273
01:10:43,856 --> 01:10:46,959
<font face="Serif" size="18">—tangible proof, concrete evidence—</font>

1274
01:10:46,959 --> 01:10:51,497
<font face="Serif" size="18">that Jehovah had not abandoned his people.</font>

1275
01:10:51,497 --> 01:10:55,234
<font face="Serif" size="18">And he did not abandon Anna.</font>

1276
01:10:55,234 --> 01:10:59,638
<font face="Serif" size="18">So not only had Anna clung to Jehovah</font>

1277
01:10:59,638 --> 01:11:04,643
<font face="Serif" size="18">but Jehovah held on to her and</font>

1278
01:11:04,643 --> 01:11:08,480
<font face="Serif" size="18">—an<i>d  </i></font><font face="Serif" size="18">rewarded her.</font>

1279
01:11:08,480 --> 01:11:11,483
<font face="Serif" size="18">This is loyal love.</font>

1280
01:11:12,985 --> 01:11:15,921
<font face="Serif" size="18">Anna’s faithful record</font>

1281
01:11:15,921 --> 01:11:18,457
<font face="Serif" size="18">is so well-known</font>

1282
01:11:18,457 --> 01:11:22,928
<font face="Serif" size="18">that some 50 years later,
50 years later or so,</font>

1283
01:11:22,928 --> 01:11:25,965
<font face="Serif" size="18">Luke was compelled to write about her.</font>

1284
01:11:25,965 --> 01:11:28,033
<font face="Serif" size="18">Where did he get his information?</font>

1285
01:11:28,033 --> 01:11:29,868
<font face="Serif" size="18">Who did he talk to?</font>

1286
01:11:29,868 --> 01:11:33,339
<font face="Serif" size="18">Did he talk to Mary or interview her
or some of the older ones?</font>

1287
01:11:33,339 --> 01:11:35,941
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘There was this woman, Anna.
She was at the temple.</font>

1288
01:11:35,941 --> 01:11:37,743
<font face="Serif" size="18">She would never leave.’</font>

1289
01:11:37,743 --> 01:11:39,745
<font face="Serif" size="18">We don’t know.</font>

1290
01:11:39,745 --> 01:11:44,383
<font face="Serif" size="18">But what we do know is
that Jehovah inspired Luke</font>

1291
01:11:44,383 --> 01:11:48,654
<font face="Serif" size="18">to record and to document
her life in His Word</font>

1292
01:11:48,654 --> 01:11:52,291
<font face="Serif" size="18">so that we could be taught lessons.</font>

1293
01:11:52,291 --> 01:11:55,928
<font face="Serif" size="18">And here we are some 2,000 years later,</font>

1294
01:11:55,928 --> 01:11:59,298
<font face="Serif" size="18">and we are using her life as an example</font>

1295
01:11:59,298 --> 01:12:02,668
<font face="Serif" size="18">of commitment and unbreakable integrity</font>

1296
01:12:02,668 --> 01:12:04,670
<font face="Serif" size="18">for you students to imitate.</font>

1297
01:12:06,105 --> 01:12:09,608
<font face="Serif" size="18">So, what can you learn from Anna’s example?</font>

1298
01:12:12,044 --> 01:12:15,614
<font face="Serif" size="18">You may suffer loss of one kind or another.</font>

1299
01:12:15,614 --> 01:12:19,718
<font face="Serif" size="18">You will come face-to-face
with the imperfections of others.</font>

1300
01:12:19,718 --> 01:12:22,254
<font face="Serif" size="18">Your feelings may get hurt,</font>

1301
01:12:22,254 --> 01:12:25,524
<font face="Serif" size="18">you might find yourself coping
with an unexpected change</font>

1302
01:12:25,524 --> 01:12:28,427
<font face="Serif" size="18">in your life that is not pleasant,</font>

1303
01:12:28,427 --> 01:12:31,296
<font face="Serif" size="18">or you may feel that you’re a victim</font>

1304
01:12:31,296 --> 01:12:34,400
<font face="Serif" size="18">of an injustice or a serious misunderstanding</font>

1305
01:12:34,400 --> 01:12:37,202
<font face="Serif" size="18">from within the organization.</font>

1306
01:12:37,202 --> 01:12:39,405
<font face="Serif" size="18">What will you do?</font>

1307
01:12:39,405 --> 01:12:42,007
<font face="Serif" size="18">This is what you will do.</font>

1308
01:12:42,007 --> 01:12:44,410
<font face="Serif" size="18">You will cling to Jehovah,</font>

1309
01:12:44,410 --> 01:12:47,346
<font face="Serif" size="18">and you will experience him
holding on to you.</font>

1310
01:12:47,346 --> 01:12:49,048
<font face="Serif" size="18">You cling to him.</font>

1311
01:12:49,048 --> 01:12:51,683
<font face="Serif" size="18">He holds on to you.</font>

1312
01:12:51,683 --> 01:12:53,752
<font face="Serif" size="18">For example,</font>

1313
01:12:53,752 --> 01:12:57,589
<font face="Serif" size="18">I recall a time when a brother
serving in a foreign field</font>

1314
01:12:57,589 --> 01:13:02,561
<font face="Serif" size="18">because of a misunderstanding
lost his privileges as an elder.</font>

1315
01:13:02,561 --> 01:13:04,763
<font face="Serif" size="18">And he felt the decision was unfair.</font>

1316
01:13:04,763 --> 01:13:06,932
<font face="Serif" size="18">He was deeply hurt.</font>

1317
01:13:06,932 --> 01:13:11,203
<font face="Serif" size="18">But his wife— He and his wife
never stopped clinging to Jehovah</font>

1318
01:13:11,203 --> 01:13:14,473
<font face="Serif" size="18">and their spiritual routine.</font>

1319
01:13:14,473 --> 01:13:16,241
<font face="Serif" size="18">Then at a regional convention,</font>

1320
01:13:16,241 --> 01:13:19,078
<font face="Serif" size="18">a brother approached him
and thanked him for the talk</font>

1321
01:13:19,078 --> 01:13:22,014
<font face="Serif" size="18">that he gave on the program.</font>

1322
01:13:22,014 --> 01:13:24,917
<font face="Serif" size="18">Well, he volunteered
in the cleaning department,</font>

1323
01:13:24,917 --> 01:13:27,619
<font face="Serif" size="18">but he hadn’t given a talk.</font>

1324
01:13:27,619 --> 01:13:30,956
<font face="Serif" size="18">Then the brother
now said to this former elder:</font>

1325
01:13:30,956 --> 01:13:34,560
<font face="Serif" size="18">“When I see your smile and positive attitude,</font>

1326
01:13:34,560 --> 01:13:37,029
<font face="Serif" size="18">“yes, you gave a talk.</font>

1327
01:13:37,029 --> 01:13:39,098
<font face="Serif" size="18">“And it was on loyalty,</font>

1328
01:13:39,098 --> 01:13:41,934
<font face="Serif" size="18">and it was loud and clear.”</font>

1329
01:13:43,235 --> 01:13:45,671
<font face="Serif" size="18">So the former elder now relates this:</font>

1330
01:13:45,671 --> 01:13:48,740
<font face="Serif" size="18">“The experience taught me and my wife</font>

1331
01:13:48,740 --> 01:13:50,943
<font face="Serif" size="18">“that every challenge or misfortune</font>

1332
01:13:50,943 --> 01:13:53,912
<font face="Serif" size="18">“does not need to represent a threat</font>

1333
01:13:53,912 --> 01:13:57,116
<font face="Serif" size="18">“to our spiritual well-being.</font>

1334
01:13:57,116 --> 01:13:59,418
<font face="Serif" size="18">“We’ve come to view rejection, failure,</font>

1335
01:13:59,418 --> 01:14:02,988
<font face="Serif" size="18">“or being misunderstood as normal episodes</font>

1336
01:14:02,988 --> 01:14:06,525
<font face="Serif" size="18">“in the lives of competent, healthy people.</font>

1337
01:14:06,525 --> 01:14:10,562
<font face="Serif" size="18">Instead of being crushed, we grew.”</font>

1338
01:14:10,562 --> 01:14:15,134
<font face="Serif" size="18">You see, the couple looked
beyond their hardships,</font>

1339
01:14:15,134 --> 01:14:17,970
<font face="Serif" size="18">and they clung to Jehovah.</font>

1340
01:14:17,970 --> 01:14:19,138
<font face="Serif" size="18">How?</font>

1341
01:14:19,138 --> 01:14:22,407
<font face="Serif" size="18">By imitating Anna.</font>

1342
01:14:22,407 --> 01:14:26,979
<font face="Serif" size="18">They were ‘never missing from true worship</font>

1343
01:14:26,979 --> 01:14:29,781
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘[in the right place],</font>

1344
01:14:29,781 --> 01:14:33,051
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘rendering sacred service day and night</font>

1345
01:14:33,051 --> 01:14:35,754
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘[doing the right thing]</font>

1346
01:14:35,754 --> 01:14:37,956
<font face="Serif" size="18">with fasting and supplications.’</font>

1347
01:14:37,956 --> 01:14:42,094
<font face="Serif" size="18">And sometimes
those supplications involve tears</font>

1348
01:14:42,094 --> 01:14:45,230
<font face="Serif" size="18">but with the right attitude.</font>

1349
01:14:45,230 --> 01:14:50,202
<font face="Serif" size="18">And Jehovah held on to them and never let go.</font>

1350
01:14:50,202 --> 01:14:53,438
<font face="Serif" size="18">The brother is still serving
in the foreign field.</font>

1351
01:14:53,438 --> 01:14:55,440
<font face="Serif" size="18">He is an elder again</font>

1352
01:14:55,440 --> 01:14:58,477
<font face="Serif" size="18">and giving memorable talks.</font>

1353
01:15:00,879 --> 01:15:05,017
<font face="Serif" size="18">So, what do we want you
to remember from this talk?</font>

1354
01:15:06,618 --> 01:15:09,555
<font face="Serif" size="18">We want you to remember this:</font>

1355
01:15:09,555 --> 01:15:14,459
<font face="Serif" size="18">When you come face-to-face with future trials
(and you will)</font>

1356
01:15:14,459 --> 01:15:19,031
<font face="Serif" size="18">or challenges in your life
(and you will, this is what happens in life),</font>

1357
01:15:22,801 --> 01:15:25,504
<font face="Serif" size="18">be in the right place,</font>

1358
01:15:25,504 --> 01:15:28,106
<font face="Serif" size="18">do the right thing</font>

1359
01:15:28,106 --> 01:15:30,576
<font face="Serif" size="18">with the right attitude.</font>

1360
01:15:30,576 --> 01:15:33,512
<font face="Serif" size="18">By doing this, you declare:</font>

1361
01:15:33,512 --> 01:15:36,481
<font face="Serif" size="18">“Jehovah, I cling to you,</font>

1362
01:15:36,481 --> 01:15:39,918
<font face="Serif" size="18">and I trust you to hold on to me.”</font>

1363
01:15:47,459 --> 01:15:50,295
<font face="Serif" size="18">Thank you very much, Brother Noumair.</font>

1364
01:15:50,295 --> 01:15:53,665
<font face="Serif" size="18">Anna is a beautiful example
for all of us.</font>

1365
01:15:53,665 --> 01:15:55,667
<font face="Serif" size="18">No doubt about it.</font>

1366
01:15:55,667 --> 01:16:00,205
<font face="Serif" size="18">Now, our final prerecorded interview takes us</font>

1367
01:16:00,205 --> 01:16:03,475
<font face="Serif" size="18">to the West African country of Ghana,</font>

1368
01:16:03,475 --> 01:16:07,746
<font face="Serif" size="18">where David and Lynne Jones
currently serve.</font>

1369
01:16:07,746 --> 01:16:11,550
<font face="Serif" size="18">Upon their graduation from the 95th class</font>

1370
01:16:11,550 --> 01:16:14,052
