1410
01:18:07,833 --> 01:18:11,903
<font face="Serif" size="18">And so in class, the emphasis was,
not on head knowledge,</font>

1411
01:18:11,903 --> 01:18:16,241
<font face="Serif" size="18">but on how we can imitate Jesus Christ
in our dealings with others.</font>

1412
01:18:16,241 --> 01:18:18,310
<font face="Serif" size="18">And I remember a couple of phrases:</font>

1413
01:18:18,310 --> 01:18:21,313
<font face="Serif" size="18">People over productivity.</font>

1414
01:18:21,313 --> 01:18:24,916
<font face="Serif" size="18">And the kind thing
is always the right thing to do.</font>

1415
01:18:24,916 --> 01:18:27,652
<font face="Serif" size="18">These lessons are still with me
all these years later.</font>

1416
01:18:27,652 --> 01:18:30,422
<font face="Serif" size="18">We were taught how to study.</font>

1417
01:18:30,422 --> 01:18:34,025
<font face="Serif" size="18">And it helped us to study in a way</font>

1418
01:18:34,025 --> 01:18:38,630
<font face="Serif" size="18">that would build a pool
or a foundation of principles</font>

1419
01:18:38,630 --> 01:18:40,766
<font face="Serif" size="18">so that when we had a trial,</font>

1420
01:18:40,766 --> 01:18:44,269
<font face="Serif" size="18">we would have somewhere to go
and dip into that pool of principles</font>

1421
01:18:44,269 --> 01:18:47,406
<font face="Serif" size="18">that would apply to any situation
that we might face.</font>

1422
01:18:47,406 --> 01:18:49,941
<font face="Serif" size="18">And it’s true
that at the time you go through it,</font>

1423
01:18:49,941 --> 01:18:52,010
<font face="Serif" size="18">you’re taking in all the knowledge.</font>

1424
01:18:52,010 --> 01:18:54,513
<font face="Serif" size="18">You don’t know when
and where you’re going to use it,</font>

1425
01:18:54,513 --> 01:18:56,782
<font face="Serif" size="18">but it teaches you the method of:</font>

1426
01:18:56,782 --> 01:18:59,284
<font face="Serif" size="18">Let’s store all this in the bank,
and then when I need it,</font>

1427
01:18:59,284 --> 01:19:01,319
<font face="Serif" size="18">I know where I can go and pick it from.</font>

1428
01:19:01,319 --> 01:19:04,089
<font face="Serif" size="18">One example that comes to mind</font>

1429
01:19:04,089 --> 01:19:09,094
<font face="Serif" size="18">is a lecture we had
that highlighted Romans 15:3,</font>

1430
01:19:09,094 --> 01:19:13,698
<font face="Serif" size="18">where it talked about
how “even the Christ did not please himself.”</font>

1431
01:19:13,698 --> 01:19:17,569
<font face="Serif" size="18">So thinking about that lecture
makes me think of a situation</font>

1432
01:19:17,569 --> 01:19:20,806
<font face="Serif" size="18">when we had been field missionaries
for a couple of years.</font>

1433
01:19:20,806 --> 01:19:23,909
<font face="Serif" size="18">We were invited
to go into the traveling work.</font>

1434
01:19:23,909 --> 01:19:26,745
<font face="Serif" size="18">So I was thinking to myself,</font>

1435
01:19:26,745 --> 01:19:28,780
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘Can I really do this?’</font>

1436
01:19:28,780 --> 01:19:31,283
<font face="Serif" size="18">But then I reflected back on that lecture</font>

1437
01:19:31,283 --> 01:19:34,252
<font face="Serif" size="18">—Romans 15:3:
“The Christ [didn’t] please himself.”</font>

1438
01:19:34,252 --> 01:19:35,787
<font face="Serif" size="18">It’s not about me.</font>

1439
01:19:35,787 --> 01:19:37,589
<font face="Serif" size="18">It’s about doing Jehovah’s will.</font>

1440
01:19:37,589 --> 01:19:39,124
<font face="Serif" size="18">It’s about the people you serve.</font>

1441
01:19:39,124 --> 01:19:40,425
<font face="Serif" size="18">Reflecting on that helped me</font>

1442
01:19:40,425 --> 01:19:43,261
<font face="Serif" size="18">to see myself
in that big picture and realize,</font>

1443
01:19:43,261 --> 01:19:47,833
<font face="Serif" size="18">‘No, if Jesus could do that,
then this is what I have to do first</font>

1444
01:19:47,833 --> 01:19:49,334
<font face="Serif" size="18">—I put the brothers and sisters first.’</font>

1445
01:19:49,334 --> 01:19:52,270
<font face="Serif" size="18">And we thoroughly enjoyed being in that circuit.</font>

1446
01:19:52,270 --> 01:19:54,272
<font face="Serif" size="18">I don’t even know why I was so worried.</font>

1447
01:19:54,272 --> 01:19:56,741
<font face="Serif" size="18">Because at the end of three years,
we didn’t even want to leave.</font>

1448
01:20:00,679 --> 01:20:04,149
<font face="Serif" size="18">The impact of Gilead
is not fully appreciated in the moment.</font>

1449
01:20:04,149 --> 01:20:06,751
<font face="Serif" size="18">But as the years have gone by,</font>

1450
01:20:06,751 --> 01:20:10,622
<font face="Serif" size="18">I do find myself reflecting on the lessons</font>

1451
01:20:10,622 --> 01:20:13,291
<font face="Serif" size="18">that were taught during that class.</font>

1452
01:20:13,291 --> 01:20:15,627
<font face="Serif" size="18">And I see how it’s shaped</font>

1453
01:20:15,627 --> 01:20:19,164
<font face="Serif" size="18">the way I think and feel
all these years later.</font>

1454
01:20:19,164 --> 01:20:20,832
<font face="Serif" size="18">So I would say, yeah,</font>

1455
01:20:20,832 --> 01:20:25,837
<font face="Serif" size="18">it’s had a life- or personality-changing
effect on me.</font>

1456
01:20:27,172 --> 01:20:30,008
<font face="Serif" size="18">When I think back of standing in that line,</font>

1457
01:20:30,008 --> 01:20:32,611
<font face="Serif" size="18">I mean, it is very vivid</font>

1458
01:20:32,611 --> 01:20:35,080
<font face="Serif" size="18">in my memory of how I felt.</font>

1459
01:20:35,080 --> 01:20:38,884
<font face="Serif" size="18">And my stomach was definitely churning.</font>

1460
01:20:38,884 --> 01:20:43,088
<font face="Serif" size="18">But these 28 years,
I have not regretted one single minute of it.</font>

1461
01:20:43,088 --> 01:20:44,422
<font face="Serif" size="18">Being with the brothers and sisters,</font>

1462
01:20:44,422 --> 01:20:48,026
<font face="Serif" size="18">serving in different forms of assignments,</font>

1463
01:20:48,026 --> 01:20:50,362
<font face="Serif" size="18">I can definitely say
without one shadow of a doubt</font>

1464
01:20:50,362 --> 01:20:52,998
<font face="Serif" size="18">that I still would not swap it for the world.</font>

1465
01:21:01,039 --> 01:21:03,375
<font face="Serif" size="18">Well, we’ve enjoyed</font>

1466
01:21:03,375 --> 01:21:06,578
